Package boofcv.examples.imageprocessing

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ExampleBinaryOps
    Demonstrates how to create binary images by thresholding, applying binary morphological operations, and then extracting detected features by finding their contours.
    ExampleColorSpace
    Simple demonstration for converting between color spaces in BoofCV.
    ExampleConvolution
    Several examples demonstrating convolution.
    ExampleFourierTransform
    Example demonstrating how to compute the Discrete Fourier Transform, visualize the transform, and apply a filter frequency domain.
    ExampleImageBlur
    This example shows you can can apply different standard image blur filters to an input image using different interface.
    ExampleImageConvert
    Demonstrates how to convert between different BoofCV image types.
    ExampleImageDerivative
    Example showing how to compute different image derivatives using built in functions.
    ExampleImageFilter
    An introductory example designed to introduce basic BoofCV concepts.
    ExampleInterpolation
    Interpolation is used to convert an image, which is discrete by its nature, into a (piecewise) smooth function.
    ExampleMorphologicalThinning
    Simple example showing you how to thin a binary image.
    ExamplePlanarImages
    Planar images are one way in which color images can be stored and manipulated inside of BoofCV.
    ExamplePyramidDiscrete<T extends boofcv.struct.image.ImageGray<T>>
    Demonstrates how to construct and display a PyramidDiscrete.
    ExamplePyramidFloat<T extends boofcv.struct.image.ImageGray<T>>
    Demonstrates how to construct and display a PyramidFloat.
    ExampleRgbToGray
    Example which demonstrates two different ways to convert RGB images to gray scale images.
